tweet: vice mayor sena magill is having some serious bandwidth issues. mayor walker says she's freezing up, too. (i'm also getting a message saying my connection is unstable)

name: molly conger
tweet: each councilor will share a statement with the community related to the ongoing difficulties caused by the pandemic.  sena says she's so proud of the community's efforts so far. (she is freezing up quite a bit!)

name: molly conger
tweet: councilor snook's connection is terrible. i think it may not be related to individual councilors' internet connections. whatever it is, it's really affecting the quality of the meeting.

name: molly conger
tweet: the first zoom city council was done with four councilors present in city council chambers (sena was very sick and called in from home). tonight we have all five councilors connected to zoom from home & the experience is much choppier.

name: molly conger
tweet: snook notes that it is still budget season but there is a lot out of our control. he speculates that the university of virginia will not physically open in the fall, which will have a serious impact on the city's finances.

name: molly conger
tweet: councilor hill says it's been energizing to see various community groups come together to support each other. it will take a community effort to get us through this crisis, she says. she too notes that the budget process & the budget itself will be seriously affected.

name: molly conger
tweet: councilor payne says it's a time of a lot of fear & uncertainty, with many people in the community facing crises, both in terms of public & personal health and economic. council has been working hard to find ways to address this - suspending utility shutoffs, loan funds, etc.

name: molly conger
tweet: payne notes that everyone is being affected but that impact isn't being felt proportionately, with low income people and people of color being disproportionately affected both in terms of infection rates and economic impact.

name: molly conger
tweet: councilor payne shouts out the incredible mutual aid work going on in the community, again recommending people check out support cville to connect with available resources or pitch in.    https://t.co/1uByw7gWTs

name: molly conger
tweet: councilor payne thanks our frontline workers - nurses, bus drivers, grocery store employees, fire fighters and others. he says we should thank them by offering them better working conditions, strong unions, and living wages.

name: molly conger
tweet: mayor walker thanks the community. even if all you can do is just try to survive, that's a valuable contribution. she, too, thanks frontline workers for making it possible for us to survive this time.  "we won't make it through this without one another."

name: molly conger
tweet: "we know that there will be great economic consequences," "every decision we make today will determine what our recovery looks like." "we can make those decisions off the backs of other people," or we can act with grace & compassion, mayor walker says.

name: molly conger
tweet: mayor walker notes that we do not live in an equal or just society. she is proud of the community's efforts to meet the needs of the most vulnerable.

name: molly conger
tweet: hearing our city councilors talking about mutual aid with such sincerity and passion is making me cry.

name: molly conger
tweet: and now the consent agenda.   there are some more issues with people freezing and cutting out, but the clerk is reading the consent agenda!  https://t.co/PfsU4C2XiX

name: molly conger
tweet: the consent agenda passes unanimously without any discussion. mayor walker notes that item C was only a first reading - the appropriation won't pass until the next meeting, so anyone wishing to submit a comment can still do so.

name: molly conger
tweet: we have a taker for public comment on consent agenda item C! it's @seantubbs. he notes that transit is being hit hard by the pandemic. thisnitem could have triggered a public comment period at the metropolitan planning org level. he doesn't want to hold the item up, though.

name: molly conger
tweet: city manager dr. tarron richardson is calling in from inside city council chambers!!  (is it weird that i miss it? i haven't been in there in over a month!)

name: molly conger
tweet: dr richardson didn't have a ton to say tonight, but that's typical for him. maybe i'm imagining it, but i felt a little digital tension...    https://t.co/PA5pYSU4za

name: molly conger
tweet: it's time for public comment. nancy is first up. (oh, nancy, i miss you!!! i hope you're staying safe & healthy - this city needs you)  nancy wants to talk about housing -- can the city look at providing grants to landlords who suspend rent for tenants unable to pay?

name: molly conger
tweet: next up is brandon collins, an organizer with the public housing association of residents. there was a housing crisis even before this pandemic - the community spent years working toward a solution, but now the crisis is even greater. "things are significantly worse now."

name: molly conger
tweet: brandon says the housing advisory committee should meet with a focus on addressing the current emergency. "what are the needs? what are the priorities? what are the resources?" coordination between government, the HAC, and landlords will be important.

name: molly conger
tweet: councilor hill asks the city attorney for clarification on the emergency declaration that allows them to hold remote meetings - they can meet for matters related to the emergency. generally, boards & commissions are canceled, but the HAC could meet to discuss the crisis.

name: molly conger
tweet: wow there is so much wrong in the world but i still have enough emotion leftover to be mad the ADU stands for both "accessory dwelling unit" and "affordable dwelling unit"

name: molly conger
tweet: we are playing all the hits at public comment tonight! we've got tanesha up now. she's concerned about people whose housing vouchers are about to expire - will those people be given extensions?

name: molly conger
tweet: mayor walker says there's been nothing from the housing authority about any vouchers being pulled (in response to tanesha saying she has spoken with several women who have lost their vouchers). she will check. she agrees that at this time, no one should be losing that support.

name: molly conger
tweet: councilor payne says the treasurer announced a few weeks ago that all late penalties for local taxes have been suspended. you can also call city hall and get on a payment plan.  "as long as people keep in touch," mayor walker says, staff is committed to working with you.

name: molly conger

name: molly conger
tweet: brian wheeler says the site is on the city's own server, so the legacy site will be kept. the old side had 2000+ pages and the new site has around 500! if members of the public notice something is missing, the city will work to restore it.

name: molly conger
tweet: aha, rory's got the update & he's up now! he wants to know what the plan is with the new city website - will the old website remain available in archived form? he's worried about documents & pages being lost.

name: molly conger
tweet: mayor walker says people who can't make this work can email in a written statement & council will read it during the meeting. "we are exploring every avenue" to keep public participation a part of these meetings.

name: molly conger
tweet: the april deadline has been city ordinance. the city can kick it out only as far as the state law requiring a budget to be adopted by june 30. the resolution passes unanimously.    https://t.co/I8oR2oWu7x

name: molly conger
tweet: and that concludes public comment. the first agenda item is a resolution to establish june 30 as the budget adoption deadline. (we've obviously missed the april 15 deadline the city normally holds to)

name: molly conger
tweet: the city attorney is offering a very dry explanation of the law pertaining to property tax rates and there is a bizarre echoey feedback loop. at first i thought it was just my brain refusing to process information about tax rates.

name: molly conger
tweet: no formal action is required because the city has decided not to alter any of the property tax rates (real property, personal property, and machinery & tools) for the coming fiscal year.

name: molly conger
tweet: the resolution adopting the (unchanged) tax rates passes unanimously. (councilor snook had some issues with a muted microphone but he also voted yes) (the weird delayed echo thing is very unnerving and kinda spooky!)

name: molly conger
tweet: this resolution would move the due date for real estate, personal property, and tools & machinery taxes from june 5th to june 19th due to the governor's stay at home order currently being set to end on june 10th.  https://t.co/eSEcXE32CU

name: molly conger
tweet: the treasurer reiterates what michael payne & mayor walker said before - the city is willing and able to work with residents who may need more time to pay those taxes.

name: molly conger
tweet: mayor walker again says they will work with people who cannot pay those property taxes. call in, communicate about your situation, "we appreciate every effort."

name: molly conger
tweet: mayor walker acknowledges that they understand a 2 week extension won't be enough for people who can't pay -- the city attorney explains that june 19th is the latest the city could feasibly set this deadline in order to balance & close out the FY20 budget.

name: molly conger
tweet: mayor walker says based on what she's seen, "it's unlikely" UVA students will return to school in the fall. it's important to have those hard conversations early on in this process to make the right decisions. our local economy is very much dependent on students & tourism.

name: molly conger
tweet: councilor payne emphasizes the importance of keeping city employees on the payroll (they're a large local employer) and keeping commitments made to affordable housing.

name: molly conger
tweet: "if we aren't strategic with this funding, we will get to a point where there is no funding to be strategic about," mayor walker says about a possible scenario in which the local wedding industry dries up, tourism stops, and UVA students are gone for more than a semester.

name: molly conger
tweet: the local emergency declaration allows local government to meet electronically only for matters directly related to the emergency. this puts a lot of local issues on pause.

name: molly conger
tweet: councilor payne says this puts some limitations on extensive changes in process for things like city funding of nonprofits.

name: molly conger
tweet: "short term critical needs will be more important than long term needs," councilor snook says about forming a city budget during the pandemic. keeping people fed & in their homes NOW will take priority over funding long term housing initiatives.

name: molly conger
tweet: vice mayor sena magill says the top priority is keeping our most vulnerable in the community safe. her other concerns are kids lacking normalcy & structure and keeping city employees employed.

name: molly conger
tweet: payne also says he hopes to reach out to the albemarle county board of supervisors to coordinate spending that money to maximize its impact.

name: molly conger
tweet: apparently the CARES act included some community development block grant money for local government. councilor payne has questions about the requirements that money comes with - what exactly can we spend it on?

name: molly conger
tweet: payne says the city can't operate in a silo - local government has to work with community based mutual aid for a coordinated, whole-community response.

name: molly conger

name: molly conger
tweet: mayor walker speculates that the longer this lasts, especially if it lasts a long time, some of the regulations will have to be relaxed, specially re: the local government's inability to meet about anything other than emergency measures.

name: molly conger
tweet: city attorney john blair says the definition of "essential functions" that can be discussed via electronic meeting as allowable by the state attorney general may change as this stretches on.

name: molly conger
